HEADWORD: demonetize
<hw>de*mon"e*tize</hw> <pr>(?; see <er>Monetary</er>)</pr>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> <def>To deprive of current value; to withdraw from use, as
money.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They [gold mohurs] have been completely <qex>demonetized</qex> by
the [East India] Company.</q> <rj><qau>R. Cobden.</qau></rj></p>

